==English==
===Etymology===
{{OF.}} ''parer'' "arrange, prepare, trim," from {{L.}} parare "make ready," from Proto-Indo-European base ''*per-'' "to bring forward, bring forth".

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: pâr
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /peə(r)/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /pe@(r)/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛə(r)|-ɛə(r)]]

====Homophones====
*[[pair]]
*[[pear]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|par|ing}}
#{{transitive}} To [[remove]] the [[outer]] [[covering]] or [[skin]] of something with a [[knife]].
#:''She '''pared''' the paired pears.''
#{{transitive}} To [[reduce]] or [[trim]] something as if by cutting off.
#:''Albrecht sought to '''pare''' his options down by disregarding anything beyond his meager budget. ''

====Synonyms====
* to [[peel]]
* to [[skin]]

====Related terms====
*[[pare down]]
*[[paring knife]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[schillen]]

